body:
This is a PR for issue https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/issues/9360. 

Note that while I'm still a little unclear about `master` vs. `types-2.0`, the naming and code leads me to believe the latter is for TypeScript 2.0, and I wanted this change to be available for users of both, so I am submitting a pull request for each. Because the content of the files I moved were different in the two branches, it would cause a conflict when `master` eventually gets merged into `types-2.0`, so I instead branched off of their common ancestor (commit `703bedf`), moved the files, then merged _that_ branch into both  `master` and `types-2.0`. I confirmed both were correct, and that no conflicts would be caused by my changes when they are next merged. If this approach was too wonky, please let me know which approach would be preferred.

**Note:** I had to change some references in other .d.ts files to point to the new location. While this should not be a problem for the tests, a few of the files I had to change were the actual type definition files; will that not break clients who get the latest Nuget versions of these, since the whole point of moving lodash-3.10.d.ts was so that it does not get added to the solution when its Nuget package is installed?

title: ssh2: Error TS2411 when compiled with "strictNullChecks"
body:
The index signature in the `TerminalModes` causes a variety of errors when compiled with the `strictNullChecks` option:

```
index.d.ts(1092,5): error TS2411: Property 'VINTR' of type 'number | undefined' is not assignable to string index type 'number'.
index.d.ts(1094,5): error TS2411: Property 'VQUIT' of type 'number | undefined' is not assignable to string index type 'number'.
index.d.ts(1096,5): error TS2411: Property 'VERASE' of type 'number | undefined' is not assignable to string index type 'number'.
...
```

The reason for this is that not all properties satisfy the index signature (most properties are actually `number|undefined`, and not `number`).
This can be solved by changing the index signature from `[mode: string]: number` to `[mode: string]: number|undefined`.
